# Routing Conventions

Full route code patterns: `docs/skills/builder-io.md`

## Critical Rules

- `app/[...page]/page.tsx` does NOT match `/` — `app/page.tsx` must separately implement Builder with `userAttributes: { urlPath: "/" }`
- Only pass `options: getBuilderSearchParams(searchParams)` on detail/slug pages — not on list or index pages
- Always set `export const revalidate = 5` on Builder-connected pages for near-real-time publish updates

## Route Types

| Route type | File | Builder fetch |
|---|---|---|
| Catch-all (Builder pages) | `app/[...page]/page.tsx` | `fetchOneEntry` with `userAttributes: { urlPath }` |
| Root route | `app/page.tsx` | `fetchOneEntry` with `userAttributes: { urlPath: "/" }` |
| List page | `app/[model]/page.tsx` | `fetchEntries` |
| Detail/slug page | `app/[model]/[slug]/page.tsx` | `fetchOneEntry` with `query: { "data.slug": slug }` |

## Three Blog Patterns

| Pattern | Model type | Body source |
|---|---|---|
| Data model | Data | `data.content` HTML field → `BlogArticleBody` |
| Section model | Section | Builder visual blocks → `<RenderBuilderContent>` |
| Hybrid | Section + Data | Data bindings in template → `<RenderBuilderContent data={{ article }}>` |
